17 - \n|}\n\n=====Commercial Operations=====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Director DE&S Commercial Operations   \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Alan Peter <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 -\n|-\n| Phil Tozer <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 -\n \n|}\n\n=====Commercial Capability=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Director Commercial Capability   \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n|Mike Greatwich <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 - \n|}\n\n=====Support=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Commercial Support  \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Steve Glass <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2019 - \n|}\n\n=====Information Technology=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Director Chief Information Officer \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Nigel Shaw <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2019  - Present\n|}\n\n====Directorate-General (Resources)====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Director-General, Resources\n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Michael Bradley <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2016-2018\n|-\n| David Johnson <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2019-Present\n|}\n\n=====Finance=====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Director Financial Plans & Analysis  \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| David Johnson <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 - 2019\n|-\n| Ann Underwood <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 - 2019\n|}\n\n=====Transformation=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Director Transformation \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n|Geoff Robins <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 - \n|}\n\n=====Corporate Function  Manager=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Finance and Accounting Corporate Function Manager  \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Rob Young  <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 -\n|}\n\n====Directorate Human Resources====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Director Human Resources\n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Don Cuthbert  <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2016\n|-\n| Daniel Griffiths  <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2019-Present\n|}\n\n=====Corporate Function  Manager=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ HR Corporate Function Manager  \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Maureen Doherty  <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 - 2019\n|-\n| Graham Addley  <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2017 - 2019  \n|}\n\n====Directorate Strategy & Change====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ DirectorStrategy & Change\n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Barry Burton <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2019-Present\n|}\n\n=====International Relations Group=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ International Relations Group  \n|-\n! Name\n! Date held\n|-\n| Valerie Evans  <ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n| 2019 - Present \n|}\n\n==Major projects==\nDE&S manages a variety of defence [[procurement]] and support projects inherited from the [[Defence Logistics Organisation|DLO]] and [[Defence Procurement Agency|DPA]] for all three services. Examples of current and future procurement projects include:\n\n===Vessels===\n* [[Type 45 destroyer|Type 45]] [[destroyer]]  [[ship class|class]].\n* {{sclass-|Astute|submarine|5}} [[submarine]] class.\n* {{sclass-|Albion|landing platform dock|5}} [[Amphibious transport dock|landing platform dock]] class.\n* {{sclass2-|Bay|landing ship dock|5}} [[Dock landing ship|landing ship dock]] class.\n* {{sclass-|Queen Elizabeth|aircraft carrier|1}} class.\n* [[Type 26 frigate]] [[warship]] class.\n* [[Type 31 frigate]] class\n* {{sclass2-|River|patrol vessel|1}}\n* {{sclass2-|Tide|tanker|1}}\n* [[Solid Support Ship]]\n* {{sclass-|Vanguard|submarine|5}} [[submarine]] class.\n* {{sclass-|Dreadnought|submarine|1}} Replacement class for the ''Vanguard'' class\n\n===Aircraft===\n*[[Eurofighter Typhoon]] [[fighter aircraft]].\n*[[F-35 Joint Strike Fighter]] fighter aircraft.\n*[[Airbus A400M|A400M]] [[Cargo aircraft|transport aircraft]].\n*[[C-17 Globemaster III]] transport aircraft.\n*[[Lockheed C-130 Hercules]] transport aircraft\n*[[Future Strategic Tanker Aircraft]] (FSTA)/[[Airbus A330 MRTT]] [[aerial refueling]] [[Tanker (aircraft)|tanker]].\n*[[Westland WAH-64 Apache|Apache MkI]] attack [[helicopter]].\n*[[AgustaWestland EH101|Merlin HC3]] support and [[AgustaWestland EH101#UK|Merlin HM1]] [[anti-submarine warfare]] helicopters.\n*[[BAE Hawk#Hawk128|Hawk 128]] advanced [[Jet aircraft|jet]] [[Trainer (aircraft)|trainer]].\n*[[Thales Watchkeeper WK450|Watchkeeper]] [[Unmanned Aerial Vehicle]].\n*[[Raytheon Sentinel|Sentinel R1]]\n*[[Beechcraft Super King Air|Beechcraft Shadow R1]]\n*[[Future Offensive Air System]].\n*[[Boeing RC-135|Airseeker]].\n*[[General Atomics MQ-9 Reaper|Protector]] UAV.\n*[[Air Support to Defence Operational Training]].\n\n===Vehicles===\n* Mastiff [[Cougar (vehicle)]] Protected Patrol Vehicle.\n*[[Ajax (Scout SV)]]\n*[[Panther Command and Liaison Vehicle]].\n*[[BvS 10|Viking]] [[armoured personnel carrier]].\n*[[Mechanised Infantry Vehicle]]\n*[[Multi Role Vehicle-Protected (MRV-P)]] (MRV-P)<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/526950/DES_Corporate_Plan_201619-20160526.pdf|title=Defence Equipment and Support Corporate Plan 2016 \u2013 2019|last=Defence Equipment and Support|first=|publisher=Ministry of Defence|year=|isbn=|location=|page=23|via=}}</ref>\n\n===Munitions===\n*[[AIM-132 ASRAAM]] ([[air-to-air missile]]).\n*[[MBDA Meteor|Meteor]] air-to-air missile.\n*[[Storm Shadow]] [[cruise missile]].\n*[[Brimstone missile|Brimstone]] air-launched [[anti-tank guided missile]].\n*[[FGM-148 Javelin]] anti-tank guided missile.\n*[[Main Battle Tank and Light Armour Weapon]] (MBT LAW) [[anti-tank]] [[missile]].\n*[[Edgar Brothers#Defence General Munitions (DGM) Project Team|Defence general munitions (DGM)]].\n* SPEAR, Selective Precision Effects At Range munitions, see for example, [[SPEAR 3]]\n\n===Other===\n*[[Future Integrated Soldier Technology]] modular [[infantry]] equipment system.\n*[[Bowman (communications system)|Bowman]] tactical [[telecommunication|communications]] system.\n*[[Skynet 5]] strategic [[communications satellite]] system.\n*Light weapons, photography and batteries (LWPB)\n\n==Main locations==\nAs of 2016 the main locations (with staff numbers) were:<ref name=\"CP2016\">{{cite web|title=DE&S Corporate Plan 2016-2019|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/526950/DES_Corporate_Plan_201619-20160526.pdf|website=UK Government|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>\n* [[MoD Abbey Wood]] (7,920) - Head Office\n* [[DM Beith]] (220) - Defence Munitions\n* [[MoD Bicester]] (140) - Logistics\n* [[HMNB Clyde]] (100) - Fleet Support and Defence Munitions\n* [[HMNB Devonport]] (220) - Fleet Support and Defence Munitions\n* [[MoD Kineton|DM Kineton]] (240) - Defence Munitions\n* [[DMC Longtown|DM Longtown]] (120) - Defence Munitions\n* [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|Ministry of Defence]], London (90) - Policy\n* [[RAF Northolt]] (210) - [[British Forces Post Office]]\n* [[HMNB Portsmouth]] and [[DM Gosport]] (350) - Fleet Support and Defence Munitions\n* [[Rosyth Dockyard]] (120) - Fleet Support and Defence Munitions\n* [[RAF Waddington]] (170) - [[ISTAR]] Support\n* [[Yeovil]] (410) - Helicopter Support\n\nResponsibility for 'Logistics, Commodities and Services' (including storage and delivery of non-weaponry equipment, such as food and clothing, to soldiers)<ref>{{cite web|title=Giant MoD Donnington Buildings Take Shape|url=http://www.shropshirestar.com/pictures/news-pictures/2016/02/21/pictured-giant-mod-donnington-buildings-take-shape/|website=Shropshire Star|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref> was contracted out to the private sector in 2015 under an arrangement that included the transfer of 1,100 staff and construction of a new 'Defence Fulfilment Centre' at [[MoD Donnington]].<ref name=\"CP2016\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Attribution==\nThis article contains text from this source: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/526950/DES_Corporate_Plan_201619-20160526.pdf. \u00a9 Crown copyright, which is available under the [[Open Government Licence|Open Government Licence v3.0]]\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/de-s-organisation-chart}}\n*[https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/de-s-organisation-chart DE&S Organisation Structure]\n\n{{United Kingdom Ministry of Defence}}\n\n[[Category:Defence agencies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:United Kingdom defence procurement| ]]\n[[Category:Military logistics of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Government agencies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:Military acquisition]]\n[[Category:2007 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Le Petit Chat", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defence_Equipment_and_Support"}
